# Source checks out LF on every platform.
#
# Several contract tests read a source file with readFileSync and compare it
# against a template literal — and the language normalises CRLF to LF inside
# template literals. So on a CRLF checkout the expected string is LF while the
# actual string is CRLF, and the comparison cannot succeed no matter what the
# file says. That split is silent and platform-shaped: canvasCssContract fails
# on a Windows clone while CI's Linux runner reports the same commit green.
#
# Pinning eol here removes the split at its source rather than teaching each
# test to normalise.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Bundled typefaces and raster/media assets must never be line-ending filtered.
*.otf binary
*.png binary
*.gif binary
